reviews.review: If you saw the 1st Star Wars movie, you need to see this one to have your closure. It’s really good. Something for everyone to enjoy. Yes it’s Disney but that didn’t change the fun of the movie in my words. Must see!
Well, this movie managed to under meet my already low expectations. The VFX were good but the story , particularly the end, was very very bad. Wouldn´t recommend paying for this shit
Great ending to episodes 4 through 8.  It's a little fast paced as they try to get as much content in as they can.
It's a shame JJ Abrams didn't get all three of the trilogy.  There is some hokeyness to line up the plot points, but, it was an entertaining action packed journey.
The story gave good closure to the Star Wars series.
A very cool way to end the series, a must see.

It was fine, it threw away some of the complexity and new direction that The Last Jedi added, to dumb down Star Wars to Jedi vs Sith again. Which, sigh. But was the first movie I really think Rey, Finn, And Poe shined. They stepped out of the shadow of the original movies, and, there will be no more. Would watch a new trilogy with just them no Skywalkers. Throwing it out there Disney.

I absolutely loved this film.  It took me back to all the fun I had in 1977 when I saw the original film in the theater as a boy.  Negativity, sadly, often over shadows the positivity films like this create for many people.  So, if you want to have a FUN time in the movie theater and enjoy Star Wars, go see it.  This is a movie about space wizards, magic, and laws of physics that only exist in made-up universes.  And it's fun.

Considering I was already pretty ticked off Star Wars Fan knowing that there would never be a reunion of Luke, Han, and Leia, I had no great expectations going into this.  That being said, I enjoyed this movie much more than I thought I would.  I'm glad that I saw it in the theater and don't regret paying full price to see it in that venue.
For a Star Wars Fan, the story line could not have been better.  This was the perfect conclusion of an iconic franchise.  It kept you fully engaged from beginning to end!
